
Installatie rtcapp uitgaande van een nieuwe windows 10 install
==============================================================

- Until everything works, test everything from a command shell.

- install (64bit) python3 from
    https://www.python.org/downloads/windows/
  For anaconda, see below

- To test, start a simple main.py program via Idle: main.py, Run

- via the commandline:
    - extend the Path so that python en pip can be found directly
        AppData/Local/Programs/Python/Python38-64
        AppData/Local/Programs/Python/Python38-64/Scripts

- pip via the command line:
     the basic commands
       pip list
       pip show pyqt5
       pip install a_module

- pip install
    matplotlib==3.1.3, pyyaml, pyqt5, scipy, pylatex

- apply matplotlib with diff_matplotlib
       (lijkt niet meer nodig)
    Change 3 lines in the matplotlib sources
    Removes unneeded errors/warnings on exiting.

- The RtcNoordApp can be found at:
    https://github.com/SietseAchterop/RtcNoordApp.git
    Downloaden zip or clone with git, see below.
    
- Basic testing from docs directory:
    - Command:  python tstqtquick.py
       - yields a yellow window
    - Command:  python tstmatplotlib.py
       - a simple plot
    
- start via python
  - in Meten/RtcNoordApp/App directory
      python main.py
    We can see the errors in the terminal
- start via python Idle IDE

- start via desktop
    Create a symbolic link on the Desktop from the file main.pyw


To create reports
==================
  Install latex, see https://www.latex-project.org/get   (MiKTeX)
    This is a document preparation system that is used for scientific publications,
    especially in the beta sciences.
  Test using tstlatex.tex
      pdflatex tstlatex.tex

  It is optionally in the sense that the program works without it, only the report
  is not created.

== Install perl
  Needed for report generation by MikTex
  Install from
    http://strawberryperl.com/
  Test with tstlatex.tex

Using video (optional)
======================

- mpv en libmpv  (https://mpv.io/)
    https://sourceforge.net/projects/mpv-player-windows/files/
      mpv-x86_64-2020....
      mpv-dev-x86_64-2020...
    zet in ~/Software/mpv en ~/Software/libmpv
    install mpv

- mympv.py uit de app is een recente versie uit python-mpv
    In (begin van) mympv.py het absolute pad naar mpv-1.dll zetten:
      if os.name == 'nt':
          dll = ctypes.util.find_library('/Users/rtc/Software/libmpv/mpv-1.dll')

Using Git (optional)
====================

- install Git
     https://git-scm.com/download/win
     inclusief bash en veel utilities!

- haal de app uit github
    git clone https://github.com/SietseAchterop/RtcNoordApp.git
    Bijvoorbeeld in homedir
    
    Scripts directory in path zetten van GITbash
       bijv. voor pip

Installing with anaconda
=========================

- install anaconda3 via installer
- start navigator, select enviroment
  - create and select new environment (myenv)
  - add channel conda-forge to channels
  - update/install
       pyqt5, pyyaml, numpy, scipy, matplotlib
         matplotlib version 3.1.3 (3.3?)

- start powershell in myenv
  - install pylatex via pip

- create links to powershell(myvenv) and spider(myenv) in Desktop.

- directe link naar de App
    open properties van gemaakte powershell link
      Voeg toe aan einde Target:
          python main.py
      Dus:
        .. myenv'; python main.py "


  



